# Force Dynamic Rendering Rule

## CRITICAL: Always Use Force Dynamic for All Routes

### Rule Overview
**ALL pages and API routes MUST include `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` to prevent static generation issues and ensure proper server-side rendering.**

### Why This Rule Exists
- **Prevents build timeouts** in Docker and production environments
- **Ensures fresh data** on every request instead of stale static content
- **Required for authentication-dependent pages** and admin functionality
- **Prevents static generation errors** with dynamic content and database queries
- **Essential for CLI commands, file system operations, and external API calls**

### Implementation Requirements

#### 1. All Page Components (.tsx files in app/)
```typescript
// REQUIRED: Add this to EVERY page component
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export default function PageComponent() {
  // Component implementation
}
```

#### 2. All API Routes (.ts files in app/api/)
```typescript
// REQUIRED: Add this to EVERY API route
export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  // API implementation
}
```

### Files That MUST Have Force Dynamic

#### Pages (app/*/page.tsx)
- All admin pages (`/admin/*`)
- All project pages (`/projects/*`)
- All auth pages (`/auth/*`)
- Profile page (`/profile`)
- Home page (`/`)

#### API Routes (app/api/*/route.ts)
- All admin API routes (`/api/admin/*`)
- All project API routes (`/api/projects/*`)
- All auth API routes (`/api/auth/*`)
- All storage API routes (`/api/storage/*`)
- Health check (`/api/health`)
- Avatar API (`/api/avatar`)
- Debug client (`/api/debug-client`)

### Exceptions (DO NOT add force-dynamic)
- **Client components only** (marked with `"use client"` and no server-side logic)
- **Static assets** (images, icons, etc.)
- **Middleware files** (middleware.ts)

### Code Templates

#### Page Template
```typescript
import { /* imports */ } from "/* paths */";

export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export default function PageName() {
  // Page implementation
}
```

#### API Route Template
```typescript
import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from "next/server";
import { /* other imports */ } from "/* paths */";

export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  // API implementation
}

export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
  // API implementation
}
```

### Verification Checklist
Before committing any new page or API route:
- [ ] Does the file have `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";`?
- [ ] Is it placed after imports but before the main export?
- [ ] Does the build show the route as dynamic (ƒ) not static (○)?

### Build Verification
After adding force-dynamic exports, verify with:
```bash
npm run build
```

Look for:
- ✅ All routes marked with `ƒ` (dynamic)
- ✅ No routes marked with `○` (static) except assets
- ✅ Build completes successfully without timeouts

### Common Mistakes to Avoid
- ❌ Forgetting to add force-dynamic to new routes
- ❌ Adding force-dynamic to client-only components
- ❌ Placing force-dynamic in wrong location (should be after imports)
- ❌ Assuming some routes don't need it (they all do in this project)

### Enforcement
- **Pre-commit hooks** should check for missing force-dynamic exports
- **Code reviews** must verify force-dynamic is present
- **Build failures** due to missing force-dynamic are critical issues
- **All new routes** must follow this pattern

